You guys should use the /qbar macro more often it really is very useful (Even more so in lag).  Generally ALL other /qbars have a macro to /qbar 1, then if anything wierd happens I can always recover quickly, without needing three hands.  You really can't rely on the dodgy keyboard capture code Mythic wrote, shift is checked when it decides to action your command, not when you press the command key.  If you want to be really fancy you can have a 3 chain /qbar on 9-0<br>
<br>
/qbar 1<br>
9. /macro 2 /qbar 2<br>
0. /macro 3 /qbar 3<br>
<br>
/qbar 2<br>
9. /macro 1 /qbar 1<br>
0. /macro 3 /qbar 3<br>
<br>
/qbar 3<br>
9. /macro 2 /qbar 2<br>
0. /macro 1 /qbar 1<br>
<br>
